	<div class="posts">
	<a name="108163706007042966">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/users/rja14/">Ross Anderson's Home Page</a>.&nbsp; I am going to be taking a course on Security Engineering this summer.&nbsp; We will use Ross Anderson's text book.&nbsp; I didn't know that he had looked at various aspects of P2P that matter to me in developing a distributed-object system that requires authentication in the exchange of scripts and establishing trusted connections for remotely-operating objects.&nbsp; There's even more on Anderson's home page, which just came up in a link from the Smart Mobs blog.&nbsp; I am going to enjoy all of this, I can tell.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#108163706007042966">4/10/2004 03:44:20 PM</a></span></div>
